payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"0da7e5aca16eb8b8dcff5f296ea212f5bedba37925c92e42a9e598b554409cc7","event_uuid":"86ca1e95-eefe-4499-b4d4-ed616888ac24","position":{"commit_sha":"29aa898fd05aa4f2a99f78450933685fefbbbc23","position":"1784761665244140001-86ca1e95-eefe-4499-b4d4-ed616888ac24"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-217_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"b3ee85f1-444b-4969-9577-fe7b5a242d7d","comments":[],"created_at":1784695341029246001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"393a98eb-bd99-46e1-8a5d-4bddcca7dda0","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"94f9-a9a0-7475-4e75"}],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nWith the port defined (S2 [rebar:ce4d-c3ca-5412-4798]) and selection wired (S3\n[rebar:94f9-a9a0-7475-4e75]), the backend-neutral core still named Jira concretely — both by\nconstructing the Jira transport inline AND by importing the vendor field mappers directly. This\nstory routes the **transport-construction** sites through the `Backend` port so the core stops\nbuilding an `AcliClient` inline, and de-hardcodes the provider-identity `\"jira\"` literals.\n\n## Scope split (recorded at implementation time)\n\nThe original story bundled TWO kinds of rewiring. They were split because the second requires a\ndependency-injection refactor that fights the standalone `spec_from_file_location` test-loader\nconvention and is independently reviewable:\n\n- **Landed here (this change):** the four transport/construction sites, the provider-identity\n  literals, and the `apply_handlers` exception-class import — a behaviour-preserving change proven\n  by the full reconcile suite staying green.\n- **Split to follow-up [rebar:4af8-2d88-719e-4478]:** routing the core *importer* sites\n  (`outbound_differ`/`inbound_differ`/`apply_inbound`/`outbound_comments`/`inbound_translate`) off\n  the vendor mappers via injection, and single-sourcing the leak-fix constants\n  (`outbound_links._RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK`, ADF-sizing, value-maps) under `adapters/jira/`.\n\n## Scope (landed)\n\nTransport/construction sites routed through `select_backend(load_config()).transport`:\n- `applier._load_acli` and `fetcher._load_acli` now return the backend transport directly.\n- `run_differs.py`'s outbound-diff client and `_attestation.build_acli_client_from_env()`\n  obtain the transport from the selected backend (fail-fast env behaviour preserved).\n- The jira factory builds the `AcliClient` with `resolve_jira_settings(project_default=\"DIG\")`\n  so the transport carries the project for every consumer.\n- `apply_handlers.py` catches `AssigneeNotFoundError` via a direct import (not `ctx.acli.…`).\n- `apply_inbound_records.py`'s two provider-identity `\"jira\"` literals flow from the selected\n  backend's `vendor` (the `validate_creation_channel(\"jira\")` vocabulary key is retained).\n- ~34 `_load_acli` test doubles migrated module-shaped → transport-shaped (assertions unchanged).\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Integration:** the full reconcile unit+integration suite stays green (behaviour-preserving).\n- **Neutrality gate:** a new test asserts no direct `AcliClient(` construction remains in the four\n  transport modules and `apply_inbound_records` carries exactly one `\"jira\"` token.\n- **Teeth:** perturbing the outbound delegation makes the characterization tests RED.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [x] `apply_inbound_records.py`'s two provider-identity `\"jira\"` literals (`:70,74`) are replaced\n  by the selected backend's `vendor`; `grep -n '\"jira\"' apply_inbound_records.py` returns exactly\n  one line (the retained `validate_creation_channel(\"jira\")` vocabulary key).\n- [x] The `applier`/`fetcher` `_load_acli` seams return the backend transport directly, across all\n  injection styles and the integration `_fakes.py` double; no seam double remains module-shaped —\n  verified by `make test` green.\n- [x] `run_differs.py` routes its outbound-diff client through `select_backend(config).transport`;\n  `grep -rn 'AcliClient(' run_differs.py` returns zero hits; covered by a new test.\n- [x] `_attestation.build_acli_client_from_env()` returns the selected backend's transport,\n  preserving fail-fast missing-env behaviour; `grep 'AcliClient(' _attestation.py` returns zero.\n- [x] `apply_handlers.py` catches `AssigneeNotFoundError` via a direct import (no `ctx.acli.…`);\n  the assignee soft-fail path still works.\n- [x] The full reconcile suite yields identical outcomes to pre-story `main`;\n  `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all green; the neutrality gate is green.\n- [SPLIT → rebar:4af8-2d88-719e-4478] Core importer sites stop importing the vendor mappers\n  (differ/apply modules) — deferred; needs the DI refactor.\n- [SPLIT → rebar:4af8-2d88-719e-4478] ADF-sizing, value-maps, and the `outbound_links` link\n  constant single-sourced under `adapters/jira/` — deferred.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py","reason":"Call OutboundMapper via Backend; drop outbound_fields import (site :63)"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_differ.py","reason":"Call InboundMapper via Backend (site :141)"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile_check.py","reason":"Drop _load_sibling outbound_fields/adf (:70,:75); use Backend"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound.py","reason":"Drop outbound_fields import (:49); use Backend mapper"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py","reason":"Drop adf lazy_load (:323); ADF-sizing via mapper"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_comments.py","reason":"Drop adf/comment_limits lazy_load (:84,:100); via Backend sanitizer"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_links.py","reason":"Single-source link constants behind mapper (:30-54)"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound_records.py","reason":"Replace jira literal (:70,:74,:156) with RemoteRef/IdentityConvention"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/applier.py","reason":"_load_acli seam + :443/:605 yield backend transport"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/fetcher.py","reason":"_load_acli seam + :371 yield backend transport"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/run_differs.py","reason":":403 route through Backend transport"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_attestation.py","reason":":82 build_acli_client_from_env returns backend transport"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/jira_fields.py","reason":"Receive relocated ADF-sizing/lossy-status/value-maps/link constants"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","94f9-a9a0-7475-4e75"],["parent","bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a"]],"parent_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","parent_status_uuid":"e11cbd0f-29a4-4c87-af89-5ab04a043a08","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["reconciler","vendor-adapter","rewiring"],"ticket_id":"6673-7636-a116-4f90","ticket_type":"story","title":"Route all core consumers through the Backend port (vendor-importing modules + the 4 AcliClient transport sites); relocate ADF-sizing/lossy-status/maps into adapters/jira","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["599a0eaa-409b-444d-8c36-fc283cbb3aca","bf416b0c-3dba